President Obama spoke with Abu Dhabi Crown Prince Sheikh Mohammed bin Zayed Al Nahyan and expressed appreciation for the United Arab Emirates' commitment to combating ISIL. They discussed the ongoing discussions of the International Syria Support Group and the progress made by the Syrian opposition in Riyadh. They also agreed on the importance of adhering to the ceasefire in Yemen and using UN-facilitated peace talks to de-escalate the fighting. Both leaders agreed to coordinate closely on these issues and stay in touch.